"It's not paranoia if they really ARE out to get me..."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/12/01 10:01:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anybody have some advice on breaking up camps?</span><hr size=1> LOL...I'm only exploiting if you think soloing purples at 31 and getting 3 mil XP per kill is exploiting...:)  Of course, if you want really fast XP, go kill purples nonstop with a good group.  But's that's another exploit....<br>
<br>
The above-described method for handling camps is ideal, except I always go for the highest mob in the camp I can handle (not the lowest).  Just swarm it, move back a bit and sit.  Be ready to run if the snarling pack of mobs and elementals comes near you.  If it doesn't, and the mobs aren't linked, then the mobs aggroed on your elemental will just turn away when the elemental dies.  You WANT to go for the camps where you get camp and group bonuses...they can be more than half the XP award!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utandaina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tandaina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/13/01 5:05:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anybody have some advice on breaking up camps?</span><hr size=1> Ah, Sciro can you kill the higher level before the mob heads for you? I've geen going for the lowest cause I KNOW my elementals can drop that one really quickly (and without me burning to much exp) then I can work my way up the ladder till I ahve a broken camp.  I'd love ot hear how you do it. :) And how you manage mana.  (OMG those pets burn through power) <p>Silverleaf Goldenthorn<BR>
Warden of Connla
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utidaljade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tidaljade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/13/01 6:34:48 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.truepath.com/jadae/Blue.JPG width=102 height=116></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anybody have some advice on breaking up camps?</span><hr size=1> Well, erm, Im not Albion but... once ya learn to recognize each mob types agro type (Bring a friend, Social, Solo and Scout) and compare it to: your level versus the mobs level, your group's levels to the mob(s) levels and number of people within your group versus number of mobs in agro radius--you'll start to understand. Cant really give a cut and paste answer though due to so many variabilites. <p><center><img src="http://members.truepath.com/jadae/bunclover.jpg"><br><font size=2 color="#00FA9A"><a href="http://sacredfire.orionsafari.com" target="resource window"> The Sacred Fire</a></font></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showMessage?topicID=199.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showMessage?topicID=192.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.emailToFriend?topicID=194.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.threadControl?topicID=194.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=ht